com.webfirmframework.wffweb.css.css3

Class MozColumnRuleWidth

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.webfirmframework.wffweb.css.core.AbstractCssProperty<MozColumnRuleWidth>
      • com.webfirmframework.wffweb.css.css3.MozColumnRuleWidth
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CssProperty, Serializable, Cloneable

    public class MozColumnRuleWidth
extends AbstractCssProperty<MozColumnRuleWidth>
    This is for Firefox. 
     -moz-column-rule-width: medium|thin|thick|length|initial|inherit;

 The -moz-column-rule-width property specifies the width of the rule between columns.
 Default value:  medium
 Inherited:      no
 Animatable:     yes
 Version:        CSS3
 JavaScript syntax:      object.style.columnRuleWidth="5px"
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    WFF
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
